fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.filter

Interface IDisjunction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ILogicCriteria

    public interface IDisjunction
extends ILogicCriteria
    Defines a logical criteria set, where criteria are combined together using a logical OR, associated with a cell structure. This is designed as a fluent API: most methods can be easily chained together to simplify filter building.

    Note: the IConjunction interface has precedence over IDisjunction. It is a logical error for an object to implement both interfaces: as this rule cannot be enforced by the Java language, an offending object will be considered to be an instance of IConjunction only, and a warning may be logged.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IConjunction
